The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | BPCL net plummets 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       BPCL net plummets 
                            
	Mumbai, June 17 (PTI): State-run Bharat Petroleum Corporation Ltd (BPCL) has announced a net profit of Rs 58.40 crore for the fourth quarter ended March 31 against Rs 670 crore in the year-ago period.        
	The total income rose to Rs 32,712.90 crore during the quarter under review from Rs 24,400.50 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal, BPCL said in a filing to the Bombay Stock Exchange.        
	The board has declared a dividend of 40 per cent, at the rate of Rs 4 on shares of face value of Rs 10, for 2007-08.        
	For the year ended March 31, the group has announced a consolidated net profit of Rs 1,769.60 crore, a 17.51 per cent decline over the year-ago period. The company had registered a net profit of Rs 2,145.20 crore in 2006-07.        
	Total income rose to Rs 1,12,410.40 crore in 2007-08 from Rs 99,107.80 crore in the previous fiscal.                                                                                                                                     
